{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, high-level interpretation models that rely on predefined human-constructed annotations, as well as automatic concept discovery, are regarded as strengths.",
    "Furthermore, we found two studies that used innovative, data-efficient approaches to address the limitations of current conceptual data availability.",
    "PCBM [88] created a multimodal method for improving concept learning tasks by combining a text encoder and language structure with an image encoder.",
    "MCD [154] pioneered a novel multidimensional approach for extracting concepts directly from the primary model in multiple directions, a significant improvement over previous works such as ACE, ConceptSHAP, and ICE.",
    "Local explanations, on the other hand, focus on individual attributes, which can be computationally cheaper but may be overlooked in a global context."
  ]
}